            "content": {
                "raw": "Also, I should note, this also adds the suppression of progress bars if you are running in IPython.  I added this because it seems likely to me that ProgressBars are useful, but *not* useful when using the IPython notebook.  I believe that is an increasing fraction of the time that yt is being used via IPython, and high enough (and with high enough annoyance factor for having pbars) that we should take this step.",
                "html": "<p>Also, I should note, this also adds the suppression of progress bars if you are running in IPython.  I added this because it seems likely to me that ProgressBars are useful, but <em>not</em> useful when using the IPython notebook.  I believe that is an increasing fraction of the time that yt is being used via IPython, and high enough (and with high enough annoyance factor for having pbars) that we should take this step.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
